The paper discusses a network architecture for distributed caching of content to alleviate the demands for multi-media traffic. This topic falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes new placement and delivery algorithms, which can be categorized under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper validates its proposed algorithms through simulations, which falls under Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
